        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 5:15PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 515 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
North La Junta. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
La Junta and North La Junta.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
